    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/529: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-15T23:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 15, 1932—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 15—8:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Your confidential 31, November 14, 1 p.m. You will note from my 35, November
                    6, noon, and previous correspondence that this idea has disappeared from
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName>’s mind since the
                    conversation which he had with <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VSRG1"
                        >Gilbert</persName>. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>
                    and I had both felt as you do that reference of this problem to the powers
                    signatory to the Nine-Power Treaty would be a mistake and had indeed stated to
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> that any such
                    advances would put the League of Nations in the position of appearing to wish to
                    escape from its responsibilities and would create an unfortunate impression.</p>
                <p>In view of the fact that the Council begins to consider the <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> report on the 21st it would
                    be useful to have any observations you might care to make on the subject of my
                    35 and previous messages.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
